    Benchmarking ‘collections’

    benchmark.Rmd

    The goal of this document is to compare the performances of some of the existing packages. See benchmark.Rmd for the details.

    We are comparing these packages with collections.

    • dequer 2.0-1
    • datastructures 0.2.5
    • liqueueR 0.0.1
    • hash 2.2.6
    • hashmap 0.2.2

    Queue

    microbenchmark(
    dequer = test_dequer_queue_push_pop(100),
    datastructures = test_datastructures_queue_push_pop(100),
    liqueueR = test_liqueueR_queue_push_pop(100),
    collections = test_collections_queue_push_pop(100),
    times = 10,
    unit = "relative"
)
    ## Unit: relative
##            expr   min    lq   mean median    uq    max neval
##          dequer  1.00  1.00   1.00   1.00  1.00   1.00    10
##  datastructures 10.35 10.81 199.95  12.62 13.36 304.86    10
##        liqueueR 14.11 14.68   7.47  14.45 14.71   3.65    10
##     collections  2.18  2.23   1.61   2.44  2.77   1.16    10
    microbenchmark(
    dequer = test_dequer_queue_push_pop(1000),
    collections = test_collections_queue_push_pop(1000),
    times = 10,
    unit = "relative"
)
    ## Unit: relative
##         expr  min   lq mean median   uq   max neval
##       dequer 1.00 1.00 1.00   1.00 1.00 1.000    10
##  collections 1.23 1.29 1.22   1.26 1.27 0.989    10

    OrderedDict

    microbenchmark(

    unit = "relative"
)
    ## Unit: relative

    collections = test_collections_ordered_dict_set_get(1000),
